<HEADLINE>
TAIPEI CITY INFORMATION DEPT. UPGRADED, RENAMED
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 23 (CNA) 05/23/07  19:50:12 (By Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
The Taipei City Information Department was upgraded  Wednesday
and renamed  the Bureau  of Tourism  and Communications.
</P>
<P>
The city council passed regulations concerning the formation of
the bureau, which was initiated during the tenure of former Mayor
Ma Ying-jeou, according to the city government.
</P>
<P>
The bureau is equipped with six departments to handle general
marketing, tourism development, the tourism industry, city tours,
media publications and media administration. The number of staff
will also be increased from the present 78 people to 120, city
officials said.
</P>
